<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1490] CJKTokenizer convert   HALFWIDTH_AND_FULLWIDTH_FORMS wrong</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1490</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;CJKTokenizer have these lines..&lt;br/&gt;
                if (ub == Character.UnicodeBlock.HALFWIDTH_AND_FULLWIDTH_FORMS) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                    /** convert  HALFWIDTH_AND_FULLWIDTH_FORMS to BASIC_LATIN */
                    int i = (int) c;
                    i = i - 65248;
                    c = (char) i;
                }&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This is wrong. Some character in the block (e.g. U+ff68) have no BASIC_LATIN counterparts.&lt;br/&gt;
Only 65281-65374 can be converted this way.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The fix is&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
             if (ub == Character.UnicodeBlock.HALFWIDTH_AND_FULLWIDTH_FORMS &amp;amp;&amp;amp; i &amp;lt;= 65474 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; i&amp;gt; 65281) {                    /** convert  HALFWIDTH_AND_FULLWIDTH_FORMS to BASIC_LATIN */                    int i = (int) c;                    i = i - 65248;                    c = (char) i;                }</description>
